The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for balancing tokens on graphs, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithm is designed to minimize rounding errors, which is related to the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on different network topologies, which is a topic in network science (cs.NE) and computational complexity (cs.SI).
